&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Trust is the first of a new breed of banks in Singapore – digitally native and focused on delivering a delightful customer experience.&amp;nbsp; You will work in a fast-paced and collaborative environment to solve new and interesting challenges each day. Together with our Trust team, you will help shape the future of our bank.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As an Automation Engineer in the Digital Workplace team, you&#39;d be able to work on and solve some of the many interesting challenges we are facing, learn new ways of working, and build delightful high-quality products for our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Job Responsibilities&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will play a vital role in ensuring the secure and efficient management of identity and access management (IAM) solutions, specifically leveraging Okta Identity Engine and Entra ID. You will collaborate with cross-functional teams to implement, and maintain IAM policies, authentication, and authorization controls in alignment with industry standards and banking regulations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to develop scripted procedures and automation of day-to-day common executed tasks in End User Computing services and endpoint management operations in an enterprise environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Role Specific Technical Competencies&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate and work with the various stakeholder to develop DevOps pipeline and workflow to automate end-to-end deployment processes to support Application Packaging, Windows and Mac OS patching and configurations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop service dashboards to monitor, detect, remediate endpoint health, and risk issues, such as endpoint posture, patch versions, and related security compliance gaps.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Further enhancement and maintaining ITSM tool (Atlassian Jira) for process automation. Creating custom workflows, managing permissions, automating processes, and providing user support request fulfilment and virtual agent expansion.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in EUC projects including Base Image upgrades, Office 365 Collaboration suite, endpoint OS optimisation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Administer Okta by doing SSO integrations with different protocols (SAML, OIDC, OAuth). Troubleshooting authentication and access issues. Manage the identity lifecycle and provisioning access to other applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Competence in error handling, logging, and monitoring Okta Workflow executions. Ability to build Okta Workflows and leverage on connectors to trigger action across applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively engage internal business and other stakeholders to identify opportunities to improve digital workspace and employee experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Qualifications&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in IT and minimum 10 years’ experience in end user computing and automation engineering role within a Banking industry.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven expertise in Infrastructure as Code (Terraform) and automated deployments via Harness, with required proficiency in PowerShell and API orchestration.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience in automating IT operations, Application Packaging using Intune and JAMF, endpoint security compliance scanning and auto-remediation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Okta Certified Administrator or higher certification preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in developing reporting dashboard for hardware asset management&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Added advantage if possessed knowledge in ITIL operation standards, endpoint security, management of group policies and security controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Trust is the first of a new breed of banks in Singapore – digitally native and focused on delivering a delightful customer experience.&amp;nbsp; You will work in a fast-paced and collaborative environment to solve new and interesting challenges each day. Together with our Trust team, you will help shape the future of our bank.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;Bancassurance Sales Specialist &lt;/strong&gt;you&#39;d be able to work on and solve many interesting challenges which we are facing, learn new ways of working, and help build delightful high quality products for our customers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Job Description&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Bancassurance Specialist, you will play a key role in driving the growth and success of our bancassurance channel by managing relationships with bank clients and promoting our comprehensive suite of insurance products. You will work closely with the bank partner to create tailored solutions that meet the financial and insurance needs of their customers, leveraging your strong expertise in insurance and sales to drive results. This is an exciting opportunity for individuals who are passionate about financial services and thrive in a dynamic, fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;The Role Responsibility:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Sales &amp;amp; Relationship Management: &lt;/strong&gt;Develop and maintain strong relationships with bank clients, driving sales of insurance products through proactive outreach and regular follow-up to ensure customer satisfaction and retention. Conduct customer needs analysis to identify gaps and ensure that customer needs are met with insurance solutions that align with their financial goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Knowledge &amp;amp; Consultation: &lt;/strong&gt;Act as a subject matter expert on a wide range of insurance products, providing valuable and accurate financial advice and guidance to existing bank partner’s customers. Stay up to date with the latest product offerings and market trends to effectively promote solutions that deliver optimal value.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Business Development: &lt;/strong&gt;Identify new business opportunities and expand the bancassurance channel through effective networking, prospecting, and leveraging existing relationships with bank partners. Build a pipeline of leads and convert them into long-term clients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Target Achievement: &lt;/strong&gt;Meet and exceed sales targets and KPIs, contributing to the overall growth and profitability of the bancassurance division. Use data and analytics to monitor performance and continuously improve sales strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Compliance &amp;amp; Risk Management: &lt;/strong&gt;Ensure proper advisory procedures and documentation while adhering to all regulatory requirements, business processes and company policies, maintaining a high standard of professionalism and ethical conduct in all interactions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our Ideal Candidate:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We’re looking for individuals with a background in financial services, sales, or client advisory roles. What matters most is your ability to build strong client relationships and deliver results — qualities that drive success and make a real impact within our team.&lt;/li&gt;
