&lt;p&gt;As &lt;strong&gt;Strategy Specialist,&lt;/strong&gt; you will have the opportunity to shape the strategic agenda of Trust Bank and help to communicate it to key stakeholders. The role is within the CEO office, reporting directly to the Chief Strategy Officer &amp;amp; Chief of Staff. You will work closely with stakeholders from all across the bank.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role Responsibility:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help to shape our bank-wide strategy, crafting and communicating our strategic agenda clearly to stakeholders. You’ll also be the bridge between long term strategy and our OKRs, helping to drive alignment across the organisation;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support key initiatives and projects as directed by CEO / Chief Strategy Officer &amp;amp; Chief of Staff. Some of these may be strategic in nature whilst others may drive shorter term tactical outcomes;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support preparation of high-quality material for Board and other key meetings;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support investor related activities and work closely with our communications team for any major media events;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Be a prominent advocate for the Bank’s culture, identifying opportunities and leading initiatives to create a positive impact.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
